 CREATE AN O/S WORKING DIR FOR LOCAL GIT REPO:-
 mkdir [working git dir name]
 cd  [working git dir name]
 git init .
 
 CREATE AN ALIAS FOR REMOTE REPO:-
 git remote add [alias for remote repo e.g. "agile"] [path to remote repository]
 git remote -v
 
 CREATE YOUR OWN GIT BRANCH:-
 git branch [new branch name]
 
 SWITCH TO YOUR GIT BRANCH:-
 git checkout [new branch name]
 
 TEST A FILE ADD ON LOCAL REPO AND PUSH TO REMOTE REPO:-
 touch file
 git add file
 git commit -m "file"
 git push [alias for remote repo] [branch local name]
 THEN WAIT FOR PULL REQUEST
 
 dont forget to sync to the remote master regularly (to pickup other people's changes):-
 git pull [alias for remote repo] [branch local name]
